sentences.chinese: 我喜欢语言方面的书，例如英语会话等等。

sentences.english: The hairdresser opens a salon, the lawyer his or her own practice and so on.
sentences.chinese: 理发师开一间发型屋，律师重操旧业，等等。

sentences.english: The regional crisis makes people tortured by heart blank and disorientation, and so on.
sentences.chinese: 出现信仰危机，人们普遍心灵空虚，迷失方向等等。

sentences.chinese: 先等等，好像我已经写了有bug的代码。

sentences.english: The school canteen provides hamburgers, sandwiches, pizza and so on.
sentences.chinese: 学校食堂提供汉堡，三明治，比萨饼等等。

sentences.english: These charts do not include counts of deserters , those convicted or executed, etc.
sentences.chinese: 这些表格尚不包括逃兵，被宣判及被处决的人，等等。

sentences.english: And so there is deformation,friction effects,tidal effects and so on.
sentences.chinese: 形变，摩擦，潮汐作用等等。

sentences.chinese: 这对容易调试，使有效，编辑，重新设计等等。

sentences.english: Why did Japanese public opinion support his visit to Japan?

sentences.english: In your spare time, you can play basketball, pingpong and so on.
sentences.chinese: 在你的空闲时间，你可以打篮球，乒乓球等等。

sentences.english: Where? Wait a minute. I thought mammoths were extinct.
sentences.chinese: 在哪里呢？等等。我以为长毛象已经绝种了。

sentences.english: You can go to Hollywood. And you can go see the museums and everything.
sentences.chinese: 你还可以参观好莱坞，各种博物馆等等。

sentences.english: Relationship between the size of the text contrast, and so on.
sentences.chinese: 关系的文字大小的对比，等等。

sentences.english: They can encrypt communications, randomize behaviour, and so on.
sentences.chinese: 它们可以对通讯加密，使行为随机，等等。
